  "texts": [
    "Existing FSSL methods have focused on two different scenarios [75]: labels-at-server and labels-at-clients.In the labels-at-server scenario, the server has the ability to annotate data, while the client is limited to only collecting data without the capacity to annotate it due to a shortage of expert resources.",
    "Numerous works have been dedicated to addressing this specific setting.",
    "SemiFL [77] tackles this problem through alternate training.",
    "This process consists of two key steps: fine-tuning the global model with labeled data and generating pseudo-labels using the global model on the client side.",
    "Importantly, the server and client models are trained in parallel to enable efficient collaboration."
  ],
